# Environment Variables

## Backend (server)
# PORT=3001
# NODE_ENV=production

## Frontend (Netlify - Set in Netlify Dashboard)
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.onrender.com

# Instructions:
# 1. For local development, you don't need this file (defaults work)
# 2. For Netlify production:
#    - Set VITE_API_URL in Netlify dashboard under Site settings > Environment variables
#    - Value should be your Render backend URL (e.g., https://universal-downloader-backend.onrender.com)
# 3. For Render backend:
#    - No environment variables needed, defaults are fine
